#compdef imgdiff
# =============================================================================
# imgdiff — Nikita Tolkachev's "Faster than the fastest in the
#            world pixel-by-pixel image difference tool" — a Go
#            CLI for comparing two images and producing a
#            DIFF IMAGE that highlights per-pixel differences.
#            Distinguishing features:
#              - PARALLEL PIXEL COMPARISON via goroutines that
#                shard the image bounds across CPU cores
#              - CONFIGURABLE THRESHOLD (0.0-1.0) for color-
#                difference sensitivity (CIEDE2000 color
#                distance metric)
#              - LAYOUT DETECTION mode (--fail-on-layout) that
#                exits with code 2 if input image dimensions
#                differ
#              - DIFF IMAGE rendering: by default the diff
#                output uses TRANSPARENT background; --diff-
#                image flag renders the original image
#                underneath
#              - Outperforms pixelmatch (JavaScript), Resemble.js
#                (JavaScript), Selenium-screenshot-comparator,
#                and similar tools by orders of magnitude
#                (per the README benchmarks: imgdiff processes
#                4K images in ~50ms vs pixelmatch's ~5000ms)
#            Used in CI/CD visual regression testing pipelines,
#            screenshot-based UI testing, and quality assurance
#            for design systems.
#
# Author:  Nikita Tolkachev (n7olkachev on GitHub) — Russian
#          frontend engineer; launched imgdiff in 2020 as a
#          fast alternative to JavaScript-based image diff
#          tools that dominated the CI testing space.
# Source:  https://github.com/n7olkachev/imgdiff
#          https://github.com/n7olkachev/imgdiff/blob/main/cmd/main.go
# CLI:     cmd/main.go — uses `alexflint/go-arg` (already
#          documented in taxonomy as one of Go's early argv
#          parsers).  Headline visual library: `github.com/
#          logrusorgru/aurora` for ANSI-colored error and
#          status output during image diff execution.
# Library: logrusorgru/aurora
#          ("Ultimate ANSI colors for Golang. The package
#           supports Printf/Sprintf etc." — Konstantin Ivanov
#           (logrusorgru) — Russian Go developer.  aurora is a
#           CHAINABLE-METHOD ANSI colorizer for Go (similar to
#           JavaScript's chalk) that distinguishes itself from
#           fatih/color by:
#             - CHAINABLE method API: `Bold(Red("error"))` or
#               `Red("error").Bold()`
#             - INTERFACE-BASED design: every colorized value
#               implements `Value` interface for transparent
#               passing through fmt.Sprintf/Println
#             - 24-BIT RGB COLOR SUPPORT
#             - GRADIENT + INDEXED COLOR support
#             - Iterator-style multi-color chains
#             - PRINTF-COMPATIBLE — colored values work
#               directly in format strings via the Value
#               interface
#           Released 2017 as the alternative to fatih/color
#           for developers who preferred chainable methods to
#           imperative `color.New(...).Println(...)` style.)
# License: MIT (imgdiff); WTFPL/Unlicense (aurora — actually
#          "BSD-3-Clause" per the LICENSE file in the repo)
# Status:  imgdiff — 1707+ stars on n7olkachev/imgdiff, active
#          maintenance; aurora — 1500+ stars on logrusorgru/
#          aurora, 80M+ all-time pkg.go.dev downloads,
#          foundational dependency of wtfutil/wtf (terminal
#          dashboard, 19k+ stars), projectdiscovery/naabu (port
#          scanner), swartzrock/ecsview, Jeifai web platform,
#          imgdiff (THIS), and many other Go CLI tools.
